article.title: Temperature structure and kinematics of the IRDC G035.39-00.33

multiple_choice_question.text: Which of the following statements about Figure 1 is FALSE?
choices: The figure shows the MIPS 24µm emission overlaid with infrared extinction contours.
White diamonds mark the locations of massive dense Herschel cores.
The dashed grey rectangle illustrates the extent of the area mapped with the GBT.
The white dashed line indicates the peak intensity ridge of CCS (2-1) emission.

multiple_choice_question.text: Figure 2 shows data products from GBT observations of G035.39. Which panel displays the integrated intensities of the NH3 (2, 2) inversion transition?
What does the yellow shaded region in Figure 5b represent?
choices: The spread area given by two standard deviations of all velocity dispersion values in the main velocity component.
The fitting uncertainty for the radial velocity profile.
The range of velocity gradients found in previous studies of G035.39.
The locations of massive protostellar cores.

multiple_choice_question.text: Equation 4 relates the optical depth (τν) to several physical parameters. Which of these parameters is NOT directly included in the equation?
choices: Mean molecular weight per hydrogen molecule (μH2)
